I, Jared G. Isaacman, declare under penalty of perjury under the laws of the United States
of America, that the following is true and correct:
1. I am over the age of eighteen years and I am competent to testify to the matters
contained in this Declaration.
2. I am the Chief Executive Officer of Defendant, Shift4 Payments, LLC. I am also the
Chief Executive Officer of Defendant Lighthouse Network, LLC dba Shift4 Payments
(“Lighthouse”). I have held these positions since founding the companies. I provide this
declaration in support of Defendants’ Motion for Summary Judgment.
3. I have personal knowledge of the following facts from my involvement in the
negotiations and my review of the documents and communications in this case.

    Case 2:18-cv-01747-JCM-BNW Document 185-4 Filed 04/29/20 Page 2 of 31
 4. In my capacity as CEO of Shift4 Payments, LLC and Lighthouse, I have become
familiar with Shift4’s business practices.
5. I understand English and I am able to read, write, and speak fluently in English.
Background
6. On May 1 , 2018, Tom Hannon and I spoke on the phone and agreed Tom would
immediately resign from Card Connect and begin working for Shift4 Payments.
7. On May 2, 2018, at 3:23 p.m., Tom Hannon sent a resignation letter to CardConnect
via email to Mike Peters and Jeff Shanahan.
8. Mr. Hannon’s last day at CardConnect was May 2, 2018.
9. After his last day at CardConnect, Mr. Hannon participated in the following text
message exchange on May 3-4, 2018 with Shanahan:
